Info.Name: Tillage
Info.Description:
Agrovoc term: tillage
Agrovoc url: http://aims.fao.org/aos/agrovoc/c_7771
Agrovoc definition:  Tillage aims to create a soil environment favourable to plant growth (Klute 1982). Definitions of tillage vary. According to Lal (1979a, 1983) it is defined as physical, chemical or biological soil manipulation to optimize conditions for germination, seedling establishment and crop growth. Ahn and Hintze (1990), however, define it as any physical loosening of the soil carried out in a range of cultivation operations, either by hand or mechanized. Soil manipulation can change fertility status markedly and the changes may be manifested in good or poor performance of crops (Ohiri and Ezumah 1991). In addition, tillage operations loosen, granulate, crush or compact soil structure, changing soil properties such as bulk density, pore size distribution and composition of the soil atmosphere that affect plant growth.(en)
